### [Instance Properties](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64#1610930)

[`cpusubtype`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525740-cpusubtype)An integer specifying the exact model of the CPU. To run on all PowerPC processors supported by the macOS kernel, this should be set to `CPU_SUBTYPE_POWERPC_ALL`.[`cputype`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525741-cputype)[`filetype`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525785-filetype)[`flags`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525810-flags)An integer containing a set of bit flags that indicate the state of certain optional features of the Mach-O file format. These are the masks you can use to manipulate this field:[`magic`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525718-magic)An integer containing a value identifying this file as a 64-bit Mach-O file. Use the constant `MH_MAGIC_64` if the file is intended for use on a CPU with the same endianness as the computer on which the compiler is running. The constant `MH_CIGAM_64` can be used when the byte ordering scheme of the target machine is the reverse of the host CPU.[`ncmds`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525341-ncmds)[`reserved`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525781-reserved)[`sizeofcmds`](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64/1525364-sizeofcmds)## [See Also](/documentation/kernel/mach_header_64#see-also)
